article.description: Olalekan Ajayi scored 17 points and grabbed 10 rebounds, and Cal State Northridge defeated Vanguard 72-52 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Cal State Northridge runs away from Vanguard, 72-52
article.linkText: Cal State Northridge runs away from Vanguard, 72-52
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- Olalekan Ajayi scored 17 points and grabbed 10 rebounds, and Cal State Northridge defeated Vanguard 72-52 on Wednesday night. Micheal Warren had 17 points and seven boards, and Jason Richardson added 14 points for the Matadors (2-2), who shot 50.8 percent from the field, 75 percent from the free-throw line, and had 21 assists. Cal State Northridge opened on an 11-2 run and extended its lead to double digits with an Ajayi layup midway through the first half en route to a 39-26 halftime lead. The Matadors kept the pressure on throughout much of the second half, opening up a 20-point lead (53-33) on a Richardson 3-pointer with 13:54 left. Antonio Bishop made a layup with 8:31 remaining which cut Vanguard deficit to 58-44, but the Lions got no closer. Jaamon Echols scored 16 to lead Vanguard. Zach Allmon had 10.
